&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NWAFT Maternity Services are committed to providing safe, quality care to all women through the promotion of normality and informed choice. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently over 7000 babies are born within Maternity Services Northwest Anglia Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide acute maternity services across 2 sites to city and rural communities that have diverse cultural and economical challenges. We also provide services to women at Peterborough Prison. We are accredited at Level 3 for the UNICEF Baby Friendly Initiative and have won awards for our breastfeeding services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to Maternity Leave an exciting opportunity for a pro-active, passionate Nursery Nurse has arisen to join our midwifery clinical team. As a Nursery Nurse, you will be expected to support our mother’s and babies along with our midwifery team to ensure that patient’s experience and quality of care are met at all times&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katrina Lilly: Maternity Inpatient Manager&lt;/p&gt;
